    dc:title "Revision of the Alitta virens species complex (Annelida: Nereididae) from the North Pacific Ocean" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1437593>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1437595>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1437597>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1437625> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1437593>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Schematic diagrams and terminology of atokal and epitokal parapodial features in Alitta virens species complex; line drawings from medial parapodia in frontal view. Atoke parapodia: A. Lectotype of A. williami nom. nov. (NHMUK 1860.2.29.6). B. Lectotype of A. plenidentata n. comb. (CASIZ 14013). Epitoke parapodia: C. Holotype of A. brandti, male (ZINRAS 6/9181). D. Topotype of A. plenidentata n. comb., female (LACM-AHF Poly 9321). Ensiform chaetae omitted. Terminology based on Hylleberg et al. (1986) and Bakken & Wilson (2005), but with some adaptations." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1437593/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1437595>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Alitta brandti Malmgren, 1865, epitoke male. Holotype (ZINRAS 6/9181), southwestern Sea of Okhotsk, Russia. A. Body, dorsal view (arrow pointing first natatory chaetiger). B. Anterior region, dorsal view. C. Left jaw, dorsal (left) and ventral (right) views. D. Pharynx, ventral view (roman numerals refer to pharyngeal areas; a, left; b, right). E. Pigmented dorsolateral surface of median parapodia, dorsal view. F. Root of aciculae (set. 60). G. Articulation of same sesquigomph spiniger, ventral (left) and anterior (right) views. H. Ensiform chaeta (set. 107). I. Heterogomph falciger (set. 7). J, K. Heterogomph spinigers (set. 35 and 15, respectively). Scale bars: A, 10 mm; B–D, 5 mm; E, 2 mm; F, 0.5 mm; G–K, 20 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1437595/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1437597>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Alitta brandti Malmgren, 1865, epitoke male. Holotype (ZINRAS 6/9181), southwestern Sea of Okhotsk, Russia. A–G. Parapodia, posterior (left) and anterior (right) views (numbers refer to the chaetiger); ventral cirri in F, dehiscent. H. Anterior segments with bulging ventral end (pointed by arrows). Arrowheads: E, black, points used for measuring entire length of ligule; white, same but for maximum width. F, white, distal and proximal ends of upper lobe of dorsal ligule. Arrows: C, black, superior lobe; white, inferior lobe. E, black, postchaetal lobe; white, prechaetal lobe; orange, distal elongation of upper lobe. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B–H, 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1437597/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1437625>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. Alitta williami nom. nov., epitoke male. A–K. Topotype (USNM 1458023), San Juan Archipelago, Washington, USA. L. Topotype (USNM 27917), same location. A. Entire body, dorsal view (arrow pointing first natatory chaetiger). B. Anterior region, frontal view. C. Same, lateral view. D. Anterior segments with bulging ventral end (pointed by arrows). E–K. Parapodia, posterior (left) and anterior (right) views (numbers refer to the chaetiger). L. Posterior region, dorsal view. Arrows: E, black, superior lobe; white, inferior lobe; I, black, lamella of postchaetal lobe; white, prechaetal lobe; orange, inferior lobe. Scale bars: A, 20 mm; B, D, 5 mm; C, 10 mm; E, 1 mm; F–K, 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1437625/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

